__fi__ Up until now , our communication with machines has always been limited to conscious and direct forms .
__fi__ Whether it &apos;s something simple like turning on the lights with a switch , or even as complex as programming robotics , we have always had to give a command to a machine , or even a series of commands , in order for it to do something for us .
__fi__ Communication between people , on the other hand , is far more complex and a lot more interesting because we take into account so much more than what is explicitly expressed .
__fi__ We observe facial expressions , body language , and we can intuit feelings and emotions from our dialogue with one another .
__fi__ This actually forms a large part of our decision-making process .
__fi__ Our vision is to introduce this whole new realm of human interaction into human-computer interaction so that computers can understand not only what you direct it to do , but it can also respond to your facial expressions and emotional experiences .
