__fi__ So in planning to be a professional naturalist — I never considered anything else in my entire life — I found that I was lousy at bird watching and couldn &apos;t track frog calls either .
__fi__ So I turned to the teeming small creatures that can be held between the thumb and forefinger : the little things that compose the foundation of our ecosystems , the little things , as I like to say , who run the world .
__fi__ In so doing , I reached a frontier of biology so strange , so rich , that it seemed as though it exists on another planet .
__fi__ In fact , we live on a mostly unexplored planet .
__fi__ The great majority of organisms on Earth remain unknown to science .
__fi__ In the last 30 years , thanks to explorations in remote parts of the world and advances in technology , biologists have , for example , added a full one-third of the known frog and other amphibian species , to bring the current total to 5,400 , and more continue to pour in .
__fi__ Two new kinds of whales have been discovered , along with two new antelopes , dozens of monkey species and a new kind of elephant — and even a distinct kind of gorilla .
__fi__ At the extreme opposite end of the size scale , the class of marine bacteria , the Prochlorococci — that will be on the final exam — although discovered only in 1988 , are now recognized as likely the most abundant organisms on Earth , and moreover , responsible for a large part of the photosynthesis that occurs in the ocean .
__fi__ These bacteria were not uncovered sooner because they are also among the smallest of all Earth &apos;s organisms — so minute that they cannot be seen with conventional optical microscopy .
__fi__ Yet life in the sea may depend on these tiny creatures .
__fi__ These examples are just the first glimpse of our ignorance of life on this planet .
__fi__ Consider the fungi — including mushrooms , rusts , molds and many disease-causing organisms .
__fi__ 60,000 species are known to science , but more than 1.5 million have been estimated to exist .
__fi__ Consider the nematode roundworm , the most abundant of all animals .
